  "final_analysis": "In the treatment of hyperthyroidism during the first trimester of pregnancy, the primary concern is minimizing the risk of teratogenic effects on the developing fetus. Methimazole and its pro-drug Carbimazole are associated with teratogenic risks, particularly when used in the first trimester. Propylthiouracil (PTU) is preferred during this period because it has a better safety profile and is less likely to cause congenital malformations. Perchlorate is not typically used for this indication. Therefore, based on standard medical knowledge and consensus, PTU is the drug of choice for managing hyperthyroidism in the first trimester of pregnancy.",
